com.alexgilleran.icesoap.xpath.elements.impl
Class AttributeXPathElement

java.lang.Object
  com.alexgilleran.icesoap.xpath.elements.impl.AttributeXPathElement
All Implemented Interfaces:
XPathElement
public class AttributeXPathElement
extends Object
implements XPathElement

Wrapper for XPathElement to represents XPath elements that describe an attribute, e.g. /@attributename. Note that unlike most implementations of XPathElement, this simply wraps around an existing XPathElement to enhance it with attribute-specific logic.

Author:
Alex Gilleran

Method Detail

matches

public boolean matches(XPathElement otherElement)

Determines whether the passed XPathElement matches all the information specified by this one.

Note that this operation does not work the same in both directions like .equals. For instance, if I call

xpathElementA.matches(xpathElementB)

Then I'm querying whether xpathElementB matches everything specified by xpathElementB. So if xpathElementB is horrendously complicated like

/this[@pred="value"]/is/a[@anotherpred="anothervalue" and @yetanotherpred="yetanothervalue"]/very/complicated/xpath
but xpathElementA is something very simple like
//xpath
xpathElementA.matches(xpathElementB) will return true. In this case, xpathElementB.matches(xpathElementA) will return false.

Specified by:
matches in interface XPathElement
Parameters:
otherElement - Another element to try to match.
Returns:
Whether the passed element matches all the information represented by this xpath.

    setPreviousElement

    public void setPreviousElement(XPathElement previousElement)
    Description copied from interface: XPathElement

    Sets the previous element to this one in the XPath expression. Note that an xpath element will retain the behaviour determined by how many slashes prefix it.

    E.g. If I have an XPath //allnode/xpath and set allnode's previous element as /element, the resulting entire XPath will be /element//allnode/xpath.

    Note that for relative XPaths, setting a previous element changes it to a standard single-slash XPath element. E.g. if I have a relative xpath allnode/xpath and set allnode's previous element to /element as above, the resulting entire XPath will become /element/allnode/xpath.

    Specified by:
    setPreviousElement in interface XPathElement
